  "prompt": "How can I get BLUE Verification on Quora?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, Quora has introduced a verification system that includes a **BLUE verification badge** to help users identify credible sources and experts on the platform. Here\u2019s how you can potentially get verified:\n\n### 1. **Eligibility Criteria**\n   - **Authenticity:** You need to prove that you are a real person by providing valid identification or linking your account to official social media profiles or websites.\n   - **Notability:** Quora often verifies individuals who are notable in their field, such as public figures, industry experts, journalists, academics, or professionals with a strong online presence.\n   - **Consistent Activity:** You must have an active and consistent presence on Quora, contributing valuable answers and engaging with the community.\n\n### 2. **How to Apply for Verification**\n   - Go to your **Settings** or **Profile** on Quora.\n   - Look for the option to **\"Request Verification.\"**\n   - Follow the instructions to submit the required documentation or links to prove your identity and expertise.\n\n### 3. **Tips to Increase Your Chances**\n   - **Build a Strong Profile:** Ensure your Quora profile is complete, including a professional photo, a detailed bio, and links to your other professional profiles.\n   - **Contribute High-Quality Content:** Write insightful, well-researched answers in your area of expertise to demonstrate your knowledge and value to the community.\n   - **Engage with the Community:** Upvote, comment, and follow topics to show your active participation.\n   - **Leverage External Credibility:** If you are affiliated with a reputable organization, publication, or institution, mention it in your profile and provide links.\n\n### 4. **Wait for Review**\n   - After submitting your verification request, Quora will review your application. This process can take several days or weeks, depending on the volume of requests.\n\n### 5. **Maintain Verification**\n   - Once verified, continue to engage authentically and adhere to Quora\u2019s policies to maintain your badge.\n\nIf you don\u2019t see the verification option in your account, it may not yet be available in your region or for your profile type. Keep an eye out for updates from Quora regarding the rollout of this feature.",
